After the suicide of Rhodes University student Khensani Maseko - allegedly due to depression after being raped by her boyfriend - calls have been made for President Cyril Ramaphosa to step up interventions to stop gender-based violence Just a few days into Women’s Month and an outcry has already started following Maseko’s death. The student was said to have taken her own life on Friday. This was just two days after a “national shutdown” march held by women across the country against gender-based violence. READ MORE: Stop withdrawing sexual violence cases – Mantashe to women Fed up with women being killed – most often by intimate partners – Twitter users decided to call on President Cyril Ramaphosa to do more to protect women and girls in South Africa.     